The Governor of Lagos State, Babajide Sanwo-Olu has honoured prolific Nollywood actress, Adebimpe Oyebade Adedimeji, better known as Mo Bimpe for her commitment to a more equal and equitable world. Mo Bimpe received the award in honour of International Women’s Day (IWD) which was celebrated across the world on the 8th of March. The actress was ranked among the top 100 women in Lagos from various sectors making impacts and imprints in the state. Taking to her Instagram page to appreciate the Lagos State Government for deeming her worthy for the recognition, she said that nothing excites her more than being recognized for the work she does. “A big thank you to the Governor of Lagos State, His excellency @jidesanwoolufor this heartwarming recognition. The Lagos government @lagosstategovt named me among the Eko 100 Women on International Women’s Day and I’m grateful beyond words. The 27-year-old actress, however, counselled young ladies not to stop pushing and breaking the bias! POLL She wrote, “DEAR YOUNG WOMAN, This is to tell you that the world is watching and you’ll definitely be celebrated, don’t stop pushing, don’t stop trying and please, don’t stop breaking the bias! Thanks again your excellency, Governor Babajide Sanwo Olu @jidesanwoolu Eko o ni baje!”.